The paper discusses the development of an online catalog of research papers that have been automatically categorized by a topic model. The catalog contains papers from two artificial intelligence conferences, indicating a focus on AI research. The use of hierarchical latent tree analysis for topic modeling suggests a focus on machine learning and natural language processing, which are subfields of AI. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which often involves the use of machine learning and natural language processing techniques. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Deep Learning), all of which are related to the topic of the paper.
